<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In working with the HTTP client, we noticed that it rejects Set-Cookie headers
that have a space before or after the "=", such as "Foo = Bar".</p>

<p>This is not strictly legal according to the RFC but we have found it to happen
somewhat often.  The popular browsers (IE, Firefox, Safari) still parse the
Set-Cookie header in these cases.  Therefore, I think we should also.</p>

